        "id": 8223
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-11-04T01:23:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "There\u0027s some tension (see comments below) between needing the sampler to exist *before* incrementalDecode is called, but the frame rect is really only knowable *after* incrementalDecode is called.\n\nPerhaps getSampler could return a dummy sampler, something that you can call setSample{X,Y} on and save that argument somewhere, but the real sampler (made by SkSwizzler::Make) only gets made in onIncrementalDecode, after the frame rect is known. Immediately after the real sampler is made, the previous setSample{X,Y} args are forwarded on from the dummy sampler to the real one.\n\nOr... if you want to skip SkSampledCodec and use something similar to SkWebpAdapterCodec, that sounds workable too, although I haven\u0027t really studied SkWebpAdapterCodec. That might be a better long term approach anyway, if Wuffs will eventually (I can re-prioritize so that s/eventually/soon/, if necessary??) be able to do its own sampling.",
