      "message": "\u003e Hmm... but what if the input stream is paused (e.g. reading over the network) somewhere where we can\u0027t completely decode the fFrameConfig? This is the \"if (status \u003d\u003d wuffs_base__suspension__short_read) { return SkCodec::kIncompleteInput; }\" case you\u0027ve added a few lines above.\n\u003e \n\u003e Even if, later on, the input stream has more data, nobody calls oSID aka onStartIncrementalDecode (and therefore this-\u003edecodeFrameConfig) again. oSID is only called once, oID aka onIncrementalDecode is the one that can be called multiple times, right?\n\nDid I say that? If so, then my mistake. oSID can be called multiple times if it returns kIncompleteInput.\n\n\u003e \n\u003e A different approach is to get the frame rectangle from fFrames instead of (re-)parsing via this-\u003edecodeFrameConfig. But that assumes that onGetFrameCount has been called (which updates fFrames as a side effect). Can we make that assumption?\n\nI considered that, too. Currently, Chromium will always call onGetFrameCount first, and so does Android. But I like the idea that it\u0027s not required.",
