      "writtenOn": "2018-11-07T18:34:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e \u003e oSID can be called multiple times if it returns kIncompleteInput.\n\u003e \n\u003e You obviously know the src/codec code better than I do, but I\u0027m still confused. IIUC, your recent https://skia-review.googlesource.com/c/skia/+/165526 \"Treat start(Incremental/Scanline)Decode errors as failures\" says that oSID returning kIncompleteInput means failure, not retry, right?\n\nFor a specific use case, yes. That is specifically for supporting Android\u0027s BitmapRegionDecoder (BRD). On Android, we always have all the data up front. Since we\u0027ll never see more data, those are failures.\n\n\u003e \n\u003e In SkCodec.h, the documentation comment for incrementalDecode (ID) says \"Start/continue... After the first call, should only be called again if etc\", which implies that ID can be can be called multiple times. In contrast, the documentation comment for startIncrementalDecode (SID) doesn\u0027t say anything about calling it multiple times being legitimate.\n\nI agree that this is confusing. But it is intended that you can call it again if it returns kIncompleteInput, and Chromium does (https://cs.chromium.org/chromium/src/third_party/blink/renderer/platform/image-decoders/gif/gif_image_decoder.cc?q\u003dgifimagedecoder\u0026sq\u003dpackage:chromium\u0026g\u003d0\u0026l\u003d286).\n\n\u003e \n\u003e I\u0027m still tempted to assume that SID is called only once, and therefore use the spy sampler approach as per https://skia-review.googlesource.com/c/skia/+/165640 \"Have SkWuffsCodec use a SkSwizzler\" (my version).",
      "parentUuid": "8d400c0e_b5a920dc",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 325,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 333,
        "endChar": 5
      },
      "revId": "8a250dc152e4a93801f77cbcb19c2e490656b67b",
