    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a87e2868_52253aac",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWuffsCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 390,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-11-05T20:12:59Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s not currently enforced, though getSampler is private, and can only be called by friends. The way we compute sampleY in SkSampledCodec, it should never be 0. Here\u0027s where we compute it [1]:\n\n    const int sampleY \u003d subsetHeight / info.height();\n\nIt\u0027s not obvious from that line, but info.height() is the height of the output, meaning we have already sampled and/or subsetted as necessary. subsetHeight takes into account subsetting, but not sampling, so it will always be bigger than info.height(), so sampleY will be at least one.\n\n(Not to say that I don\u0027t think we should enforce it; just that I don\u0027t think we currently have an issue.)\n\n[1] https://skia.googlesource.com/skia.git/+/32526b5cb0e3ad65610f3be68f9e54ae1f0cd88a/src/codec/SkSampledCodec.cpp#208",
      "parentUuid": "e6df0841_a914c22f",
      "revId": "8a250dc152e4a93801f77cbcb19c2e490656b67b",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "970ab650_e31a9a13",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWuffsCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 399,
      "author": {
        "id": 8223
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-11-07T01:38:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "When would (dstY \u003e\u003d scaledHeight)? Or is this a paranoid defensive check??\n\nOr is this something like, even without sampling, you can pass in a dstInfo smaller than the underlying image file\u0027s dimensions, and we automatically crop (without buffer overflow). But if that\u0027s the case, shouldn\u0027t we do this regardless of whether (sampleY !\u003d 1)?",
      "revId": "8a250dc152e4a93801f77cbcb19c2e490656b67b",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "2877b4b1_01363b4a",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWuffsCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 399,
      "author": {
        "id": 8223
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-11-07T01:44:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Oh, I see. From my previous example, if sampleY is 16 and the unscaled height is 30, then row 24 would pass the rowNeeded check, but its dstY (24 / 16, which is 1) would equal or exceed the scaledHeight (1).\n\nIf we rationalized the get_scaled_dimension + rowNeeded + get_start_coord formulae, as per my other comment, we could possibly remove this check...",
      "parentUuid": "970ab650_e31a9a13",
      "revId": "8a250dc152e4a93801f77cbcb19c2e490656b67b",
